    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Description\n\nI'm using Nvim 0.11.6 / LazyVim on macOS. I'm trying to activate a Julia environment via the `LspJuliaActivateEnv` command. I followed the installation instructions and julials appears to be working correctly. However, `LspJuliaActivateEnv` followed by any environment name (I tried `.`, folder names, and no argument at all) results in\n\n```lua\nError executing Lua callback: Vim:E731: Using a Dictionary as a String\nstack traceback:\n\t[C]: in function 'expand'\n\t...po/.local/share/nvim/lazy/nvim-lspconfig/lsp/julials.lua:46: in function <...po/.local/share/nvim/lazy/nvim-lspconfig/lsp/julials.lua:28>\n```\n\nI'm pretty sure this used to work.\n\nI am not using Mason. To install the language server, I created a Julia environment `@nvim-lspconfig` and installed the required packages (LanguageServer, SymbolServer and StaticLint).\n\nIn my Nvim config, I simply have\n```lua\nvim.lsp.enable(\"julials\")\n```\n\nI hope this is enough information to diagnose the issue. I'm not sure how to debug this on my end.\n\nThanks in advance for any help!",
